<hr />

<p>You read the reviews for the Tofugu podcast. It’s nice other people like the podcast, you think, but what about me and my unique and complicated tastes? What if…</p>

<p>You’re learning Japanese? <em><a href="podcast#page-34-you-are-learning-japanese">Turn to page 34.</a></em></p>

<p>You’re planning to travel to Japan? <em><a href="podcast#page-98-you-are-planning-to-travel-to-japan">Turn to page 98.</a></em></p>

<p>You’re already in Japan? <em><a href="podcast#page-342-youre-already-in-japan">Turn to page 342.</a></em></p>

<p>None of the above applies to you. <em><a href="podcast#page-299-none-of-the-above-applies-to-you">Turn to page 299.</a></em></p>

<hr />

<h4 id="page-34-you-are-learning-japanese">Page 34: You are learning Japanese</h4>

<p>The Tofugu podcast doesn’t teach you Japanese, but it will tell you <em>how</em> to study more effectively. We’ve covered topics such as:</p>
